---
// src/components/FAQ.astro
---

<section class="py-24 bg-white border-t border-slate-200" id="faq">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        
        <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-blue-600 font-bold tracking-widest text-xs uppercase mb-4">
        Common Questions
    </h2>
    <h3 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6 tracking-tight">
        Straight Answers.
    </h3>
    <p class="text-slate-500 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Everything you need to know about pricing, timeline, and tech.
    </p>
</div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
            
            <details name="faq-group" class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden open:bg-white open:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300">
                <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none text-slate-900 font-bold text-lg">
                    <span>Why is this better than Google Ads?</span>
                    <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-500"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
                    </span>
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                    Google Ads is like <strong>renting</strong>. You pay every month, and the moment you stop paying, the traffic stops. 
                    Stegg is like <strong>buying property</strong>. You pay once to build the asset, and it generates organic traffic for years with minimal maintenance.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details name="faq-group" class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden open:bg-white open:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300">
                <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none text-slate-900 font-bold text-lg">
                    <span>I have a website. Do I need to delete it?</span>
                    <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-500"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
                    </span>
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                    <strong>No.</strong> That is what the <strong>Sidecar</strong> plan is for. We build a "Marketing Wing" that runs parallel to your main site. 
                    We use a "Zero-Touch" integration, meaning we don't need your login password and we don't touch your existing code. We simply funnel the new traffic to your WhatsApp.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details name="faq-group" class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden open:bg-white open:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300">
                <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none text-slate-900 font-bold text-lg">
                    <span>Are there really no monthly fees?</span>
                    <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-500"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
                    </span>
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                    There are <strong>no management fees</strong>. You pay the one-time build fee. 
                    After the first 12 months, there is a standard <strong>RM 600/year</strong> fee to cover server hosting, security updates, and keeping your site online. That's it.
                </div>
            </details>

             <details name="faq-group" class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden open:bg-white open:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300">
                <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none text-slate-900 font-bold text-lg">
                    <span>Who pays for the Domain Name?</span>
                    <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-500"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
                    </span>
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                    <strong>You do.</strong> We insist that you purchase the domain (e.g., `yourbusiness.com`) yourself so that <strong>you own 100% of the asset</strong>. 
                    It costs about RM 80/year. If you don't know how, we will guide you through it, but the account will be yours.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details name="faq-group" class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden open:bg-white open:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300">
                <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none text-slate-900 font-bold text-lg">
                    <span>How long does it take to see results?</span>
                    <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-500"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
                    </span>
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                    Unlike ads (which are instant but expensive), SEO is an investment. You will typically see pages indexing within 2-4 weeks. 
                    Significant traffic growth usually happens between months 3-6 as Google trusts the new content.
                </div>
            </details>

        </div>

    </div>
</section>